        "description": "<p>The plugin is the shortcode (list-view-posts) for comprehensively displaying the list view for pages and posts .</p>\n<h4>Document</h4>\n<p>Please see the <a href=\"https://info.cseas.kyoto-u.ac.jp/en/links-en/plugin-en/wordpress-dev-info-en/list-view-posts\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">documentation</a> in detail. If you want to read the document in Japanese, please see <a href=\"https://info.cseas.kyoto-u.ac.jp/links-ja/plugin-ja/wordpress-dev-info/list-view-posts\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Japanese documentation</a>.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin folder to /wp-content/plugins/ directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin in your WordPress admin panel.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='how%20to%20adjust%20a%20design%20and%20layout'>\nHow to adjust a design and layout\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Please describe a CSS code in the style.css or CSS files in your theme.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.8</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 6.1 with PHP8.2</li>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 6.5.2 with PHP8.3.6</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.7</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>WordPress 4.x support was ended.</li>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 5.6 with PHP7.4</li>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 5.8</li>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 6.0 with PHP8.0</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.6</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed the waring in get_taxonomy_template function.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 5.3.2 with PHP7.4</li>\n<li>Fixed the issue that the warning message is displayed when WPML plugin is disabled.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 5.2.2 with PHP7.3</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tested up WordPress 4.9.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed the security of &#8220;hook_secret_key&#8221; shortcode option.</li>\n<li>Migrated the category processing code to library class.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed same error processing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First Released.</li>\n</ul>\n"
